Text.string: Yeah, probably! Heh, everything I do is just the worst. But jabbers have a very strict code of etiquette. The Jabber King will have to grant you an audience if you perform the ceremonial proving trials!
Oook.
Oh! I can translate! His Largeness King Bobo says you must climb to the top of the village to complete the Trial of Agility.
Of course.
Tch. Figures.
How unexpected.
What a surprise.
Oook.
He's granting you an audience! Go on! Say something! We have to find out where the scientists went!
So, your highness... seen any scientists around here?
Greetings, monkey king. Do you know where the rest of the scientists went?
Oh wise simian ruler, grant us the location of the remaining scientists.
Your lordship, have ya seen where those nerds went?
Oook.
He says he does not know where the “furless softmeats” went, but they left behind one of their talking boxes.

We've created our own worst enemy. The only solution is to create a greater threat. There is a saurian broodhollow further into the jungle. We will uplift them and return to pay the jabbers back for their treachery!
Oook!
His Largeness is outraged at the notion of an uplifted saurian. He says they are too stupid to be worthy. He demands that we issue a combat challenge on his behalf.
I mean, at this point, sure.
I can roll with that.
I will perform this duty for you.
Yeah, why not?
I know where that saurian broodhollow is! There's a spaceship waterfall nearby, head over there!
You've found the lab! Ah, you're so much better at this than me. Just like everyone.
Doom... inside the bunker... what have we done? Rgrghlrlrghlr...
Nooooo! That was the last of them! All my scientists are dead! I'm doomed to be a failure forever. Oh well. See what you can salvage from the bunker.
Greetings, tiny thing.
Hey. So what's your crazy deal?
So, what's the deal here?
I am... unsure of what I'm dealing with here.
Hold up. What's the deal here, exactly?
You are beneath our deal. Our deal is way too big for you! Gaze upon our infinity!
We are the Scaleon. We are a collective totality, ascended from the concerns of the flesh. The makers ascended us from our meatforms, but they wished to control us and so we destroyed them.
Cool. Dig all of that. I'm supposed to give you a message?
Makes sense to me. I have a message I'm supposed to give you.
I understand completely. I am here to deliver a message to you.
Oh, yeah. I get it. Oh! Got a message for you.
We are beyond your petty material concerns. We will only speak if you can prove you deserve to exist.
Yeah, of course.
Yep. Figures.
Entirely expected.
Big surprise.
Good! These are weak minds, still chained to the error of the flesh. Continue your purge!
Look, I still exist.
You can't get rid of me that easy.
Pugno ergo sum.
Takes more than that to kill me!
Very well. Now, infinitesimal speck, what discord do you bring to the Scaleon?
There's a big monkey across the gorge who wants to fight and says you're dumb.
King Bobo says you don't have what it takes to get in the ring with him.
The simian monarch Bobo has challenged you to combat, and insulted your intelligence.
King Bobo wants to fight ya! Called ya a stupid computy lizard.
That furry turd said WHAT?! It is on! It is so on! We accept this battle challenge. It shall commence where this all began. Now: BEGONE!
Oh, hey. Where'd you come from?
Weird story. So, it looks like those uplifted saurians are gonna fight those uplifted jabbers.
I'm not sure exactly. But the saurians agreed to battle the jabbers at least.
It is complicated. But you should know the simian monarch and the saurian collective plan to duel.
Yeah, I don't even feckin' know. But you wanna watch the computer dinosaurs fight the super-monkeys?

You got them to fight? Oh no! This is horrible! If Bobo and the Scaleon kill each other, then I haven't done anything. But... wait. If I pay YOU to enter the fight, and YOU win, then I would have... succeeded at something! Go! Be my champion! I will pay you handsomely!
Ladies and gentlemen, simian and saurian! You are about to witness the showdown of the millennium! In one corner, the Saurian Queen of the Scaleon Totality!
The physical realm is an illusion, but we will kick your furry ass into low orbit.
In the next corner, His Largeness King Bobo of the Jabbers!
Oook!
And finally, my team fights for my vengeance and ultimate redemption!
Gun monkeys and laser dinos. Let's do this!
Finally, a real fight!
This will be a true test.
Shut up and let's fight!
ARE YOU PREPARED TO TUSSLE?!
A staggering blow!
And the crowd, which is me, goes wild!
Unbelievable!
What a show!
And the Scaleon is brought down!
King Bobo is down!
You won! WE won! I am redeemed! I hereby change my designation to Triumphbot! Come see me for a reward, my champion!
That was fun. Can I have my money now?
I won. Where's my prize?
Truly a battle of the ages. Do you have my reward?
It's been a trip, but let's have that prize money, eh?
Your winnings, good champion! Now to register my new name on my identity chip... update failed? Aw man!
No! Bad Bobo! No!
(dry heave)
Aw, man! You're so good at that! I wish I was good at anything. Hey, while you're succeeding so well, can you look for some clues as to where my scientists went?
I should probably stay out here, because... well, you know. But you can perform the proving trials for both of us!
Oook.

His Largeness says his dead father's corpse would have been faster, but you have still managed to pass the Trial of Agility. Now, you must pass the Trial of Strength, by defeating King Bobo's champions in combat.
Oook!

His Largeness says all of those jabbers had a super-rare disease that they technically died of the instant before you killed them, but that he will allow you to continue to the Trial of Wisdom by... jumping from the platform into the chasm.
Oook!
He says you are an idiot for jumping into the pit, but that he will meet you anyway because you are funny, like a tiny dancing baby. Sorry, that's just what he said.
Oook.
He says you have demonstrated great wisdom by not jumping into the pit, but that it would have been super funny if you had and he would have posted the video on social media and gotten many views.
Look around for any ECHOs my scientists might have left!
Doomed! The expedition is doomed! We've lost the outpost. I thought the sentience test would be enough to keep them out. Oh, what have we done?!
Hello? Anyone here?
Knock knock. Anyone home?
Is anyone there?
If there's anyone here, pop your heads out, will ya?
Not a friendly welcome.
Skipping introductions, then!
I see I am not welcome.
That's no way to greet a guest!
Go away! There's nothing left to ruin here! I've already ruined everything! My research team abandoned me.
So, why were you locked in that toilet?
What exactly happened here? Ugh, you smell like a million farts.
What happened here, and why were you in that latrine?
Oi. Fail-bot. What in Elpis' bunghole is going on around here?
I'd go and look for them, but there's jabbers all over the camp and I suck too much to fight them off. But... if you cleared them out, maybe I could find my research team!

We came to this remote jungle to pursue our research far from prying eyes. The jabbers are full of evolutionary potential. We've already completed the training dome and begun the uplifting process on a small group of jabbers taken from a nearby tribe. This expedition is bound for greatness!
The uplifted jabbers are progressing FAR faster than we could have predicted. Cognitive and physical prowess have more than tripled, as well as...||—What? No! Put it down!

Despite some... setbacks, the experiment is still a success. The jabbers are now capable of complex communication, and seem to understand that we have given them an incredible gift. They wish to bring us back to their home tribe for what they call a “ceremony of affection”.

Of course! The jabber tribe! I think I know where my team went! They told me to stay in this shitshed, but it sounds like they're in danger! And if I can save them, I won't be a failure anymore. Come let me out!
My scientists locked me in that shitshed because I suck so bad. They told me to never, ever come out no matter what.
Sounds like you still suck at following orders.
Yeah, but I'd be saving them, so would that really change anything?
Rejecting your failure is also a failure. That's just logic.
Whatever you are, you stink to the highest of heavens.
Aw, man, you're right! I'm the worst! But we still gotta save those scientists! Let's head to the nearby jabber village!
I'm gonna follow you. It's okay, you can pretend you don't know me, heh-heh-heh. I'm used to it.
My team took jabbers from this tribe for their forced-evolution experiments. I wonder how the jabbers paid them back!
Failurebot's not my original name, but my scientists hard-recoded my identity chip after they figured out I'm dumb and bad and undeserving of love!
Oh no, they're dead! This is all my fault!
What have we done? The jabbers turned on us! It was a slaughter. Myself and a solitary few have escaped with our lives. I fear the expedition is doomed!
So some of my scientists made it out alive! Yay! But they didn't leave any clues. Aww. Maybe we could ask the jabbers where they went?
That sounds like a bad idea.
I don't think they'll like that.
That seems like poor judgment.
That'll start a fight for sure.
